creator: Sir Arthur Conan Doyle
description:
LibriVox recording of Round the Red Lamp: Being Facts and Fancies of Medical Life by Sir Arthur Conan Doyle.
Read in English by Peter John Keeble; Greg Giordano; Anna Simon; Lynne Thompson; Lori Arsenault; Tanica; Dewaldo; Suprada Urval; Leanne; Claudia Salto
This is a collection of short stories focussing on the problems that present themselves to physicians and surgeons in the course of their work. The volume is named "Round the Red Lamp" as a reference to the red lamps that marked general practitioner's offices in Arthur Conan Doyle's times. - Summary by Carolin
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

M4B Format Available
